  ${
    $d k y F $.  $d y M $.  $d y N $.
    fsumserz.1 $e |- F e. _V $.
    $( A finite sum expressed in terms of a partial sum of an infinite series.
       The recursive definition of follows as ~ fsum1i and ~ fsump1i , which
       should make our notation clear and from which, along with closure
       ~ fsumcl , we will derive the basic properties of finite sums. $)
    fsumserz $p |- ( N e. ( ZZ>= ` M ) -> sum_ k e. ( M ... N ) ( F ` k ) =
                    ( ( <. M , + >. seqz F ) ` N ) ) $=
      ( vy cuz cfv wcel cfz co cv csu caddc cop wceq copab cz cres cseqz dffsum
      eluzel2 addex seqzres2 syl fveq1d eqtrd ) DCGHIZCDJKALBHZAMDCNOZFLUIPAFQR
      STKZHDUJBTKZHFUIACDUAUHDUKULUHCRIUKULPCDUBFNABCUCEUDUEUFUG $.
      $( [11-Dec-2005] $)
  $}

  ${
    $d j x F $.  $d x M $.  $d x N $.  $d j k x $.
    fsumserzf.1 $e |- F e. _V $.
    fsumserzf.2 $e |- ( x e. F -> A. k x e. F ) $.
    $( Version of ~ fsumserz with a bound-variable hypothesis instead of a
       distinct variable condition. $)
    fsumserzfi $p |- ( N e. ( ZZ>= ` M ) -> sum_ k e. ( M ... N ) ( F ` k )
                   = ( ( <. M , + >. seqz F ) ` N ) ) $=
      ( vj cuz cfv wcel cfz co cv csu caddc cop cseqz ax-17 hbfv fveq2 fsumserz
