  ${
    $d x y A $.  $d k y B $.  $d k x M $.  $d k x y N $.
    fsump1i.1 $e |- A e. _V $.
    fsump1i.2 $e |- B e. _V $.
    fsump1i.3 $e |- ( k = ( N + 1 ) -> A = B ) $.
    $( The addition of the next term in a finite sum of ` A ( k ) ` is the
       current term plus ` B ` i.e. ` A ( N + 1 ) ` . $)
