  ${
    $d j z A $.  $d j x z B $.  $d j k z M $.
    fsum1fi.3 $e |- ( x e. B -> A. k x e. B ) $.
    fsum1fi.4 $e |- ( k = M -> A = B ) $.
    $( The finite sum of a term ` A ( k ) ` from ` M ` to ` M ` (i.e. a sum
       with only one term) is ` A ( M ) = B ` , where ` k ` is effectively not
